Evan Almloff

Software Developer
Show More
Company
DioxusLabs
Bio
Evan Almloff is a software engineer at DioxusLabs. In his current role, he is working on making fullstack UI in Rust easy through ergonomic design and tooling while maintaining type safety throughout the application. He has created several key libraries in the Rust web development ecosystem including Manganis, a library for asset collection and optimization, and sledgehammer-bindgen, the fastest Javascript binding library for Rust. He is also the creator of Kalosm, an open-source framework for controllable language, audio, and image models in Rust.

Rik Arends

Founder of Makepad
Show More
Company
Makepad
Bio
With 20+ years’ experience as a C/C++, JavaScript and more recently Rust developer, I' ve always been excited by using computation for visuals and audio. For this to work you need performance, and a smooth workflow enabled by the right tooling. After having everything I wanted with C except stable code I moved to JavaScript and web technologies. However, this never got to the point of being able to make fast applications that use modern CPU and GPU power. Now with Rust we have a new chance. I' ve been an entrepreneur my entire life building VJ software in the 00' s, then web UI technology and web IDEs with Cloud9, and am now reimagining the developer workflow in Rust with Makepad.

Jim Blandy

Author of Programming Rust
Show More
Company
Mozilla
Bio
Jim Blandy has been writing Free software since 1990. He has been a maintainer of GNU Emacs and GDB, and is one of the original designers of the Subversion version control system. With Jason Orendorff and Nora Tindall, he is a co-author of Programming Rust, published by O' Reilly. He joined Mozilla in 2008, and is currently technical lead of the Firefox WebGPU team, a member of the W3C WebGPU Working Group, and a leading contributor to the WGPU Rust crates. He lives in Portland, Oregon.

Kevin Boos

Principal Architect at Futurewei
Show More
Company
Futurewei Technologies
Bio
Kevin Boos is currently a software architect at Futurewei and the tech lead of Project Robius, an open-source Rust framework for developing immersive, fully-featured applications in Rust that run seamlessly across multiple platforms, including mobile. Previously, he created Theseus OS, an open-source OS written from scratch in Rust that rethinks the structure and implementation strategy of OSes, with an emphasis on maximizing language mechanisms for compile-time safety and verifiable correctness. Kevin obtained his PhD from Rice University with a focus on OS design, with other interests spanning the domains of I/O virtualization, device drivers, mobile VR, static analysis, and safe languages.

Gary Bradski

Founder of OpenCV
Show More
Company
OpenCV
Bio
Gary is founder & chairman of OpenCV.org (400M downloads in 2023). He was a professor at Stanford CS (2006-2012). Gary also ran the computer vision team for Stanley, the robot that won the DARPA Grand Challenge, now in the Smithsonian Museum in D.C which started the modern autonomous driving industry. Gary has founded 5 Startups and a nonprofit: OpenCV.org and currently sits on several boards and advisorships. He is an active angel investor, his most recent exit was Lambda Labs 2024 2nd market in $1.5B C round where he was the first investor. Gary has about 100 patents and papers including several best papers. He won the 2014 IEEE PAMI prize for contributions to the field of computer vision and won the 2021 CCV Helmholtz Prize Test of Time Award for his “ORB” paper.

Deputy Director of the Institute of Software
Show More
Company
Tsinghua Univeristy
Bio
Yu Chen is currently an associate professor and doctoral supervisor at the Department of Computer Science and Technology, Tsinghua University, as well as the Deputy Director of the Institute of Software within the same department. Additionally, he has been a visiting scholar at MIT EECS. He serves as a standing committee member of the System Software Special Committee of the China Computer Federation. His main research areas include operating systems, principles of compilers, program analysis, system reliability, and performance optimization. He has led and participated in various projects, including those funded by the National Natural Science Foundation of China, the 863 Program, and key special projects of the Ministry of Science and Technology. Chen Yu has published over sixty high-level academic papers and has taken on roles such as chair or program committee member for influential domestic and international academic conferences. He is responsible for teaching courses on operating systems and advanced operating systems at the Department of Computer Science and Technology, Tsinghua University.

Rui Zhao

Post-Doc Researche at the Department of Computer Science at University of Oxford
Show More
Company
University of Oxford
Bio
Dr. Rui Zhao is a postdoctoral researcher at the Department of Computer Science, University of Oxford. He works in the EWADA project (Ethical Web and Data Architecture in the Age of AI; https://ewada.ox.ac.uk/), led by Prof. Sir Nigel Shadbolt and Prof. Sir Tim Berners-Lee, with a close connection to decentralised architectures like Solid (Social Linked Data). His main research is centred around a) the connection between user autonomy and privacy-preserving computation, and b) facilitating data governance in decentralised multi-stakeholder contexts, through formal Data Terms of Use. Rui is interested in distributed/decentralised systems, formal modelling and reasoning, user autonomy, and balancing individuals' and societal collective interests. Before Oxford, Rui received his PhD degree from the University of Edinburgh in 2022, under the supervision of Prof. Malcolm Atkinson, where he worked on formal modelling and automated reasoning of data-use policies (/ data-governance rules) in decentralised research contexts (eScience). He obtained his master degree in 2017 also at the University of Edinburgh, and his bachelor' s degree from Northwest A& F University (2016).

Company
Sany Group' s Yun Innovative Lab
Bio
Baigui Sun, a Master of Computer Science from Zhejiang University, completed his degree in 2014 under the guidance of Professors Guofeng Zhang and Hujun Bao. He brings a wealth of experience to the field, with over ten years at Alibaba dedicated to AI research and development. His tenure included a three-year stint with Taobao' s Technology and Search Business Divisions, as well as a seven-year role at Alibaba' s DAMO Academy and Tongyi. He has been recognized with accolades such as the Taobao Technology Best Newcomer Award and the Alibaba Open Source Pioneer Award. His contributions to the field are marked by his work on groundbreaking applications: Pailitao, pioneering the large-scale application of image search in e-commerce and setting industry standards. DeepCTR, an innovative deep learning-based search recommendation system that has been a trendsetter in the industry. Face Recognition, which is widely applied in DingTalk' s attendance machines and the Alibaba Cloud API. FaceChain, an open-source project that has gained popularity for its digital human portrait features. His expertise has been acknowledged through six championship titles in the WiderFace detection challenge and a collection of six additional awards for his open-source projects and individual achievements. He has co-authored more than 30 top conference and journal papers, and his open-source projects have earned over 8,900 stars. For more information, visit his website at https://sunbaigui.github.io. Presently, Baigui Sun serves as the Chief Architect at Sany Group' s Yun Innovative Lab, where he continues to drive innovation and technological advancement.

Yanzhi Wang

Professor
Show More
Company
Northeastern University
Bio
Yanzhi Wang is Professor in the Department of Electrical and Computer Engineering at Northeastern University, a senior member of IEEE. His research interests focus on real-time and energy-efficient deep learning and artificial intelligence systems, especially on efficient large language models and large-scale generative AI systems. He ranks No. 1 in CSRankings at Northeastern University in the past 5 years and around No. 35 throughout the U.S. His research works have been cited over 20,000 times. He has received six Best Paper Awards and another 12 Best Paper Nominations. He has received the U.S. Army Research Office Young Investigator Program Award (YIP), IEEE TC-SDM Early Career Award, Asia Pacific Signal and Information Processing Association Distinguished Leader Award, Massachusetts Acorn Innovation Award, design contest awards from multiple conferences, and other research awards from Google, MathWorks, etc. His research work has been reported and cited by around 500 media. He has 14 academic descendants as tenure-track faculty at U.S. and China universities such as University of Minnesota, University of Science and Technology China, Clemson University, University of Georgia, etc.

Yan Zhou

Chief Technology Planning and Pre-Research Expert
Show More
Company
Huawei Technologies
Bio
Chief Technology Planning and Pre-research Expert of Huawei Device. He has worked in the R& D field for 25 years. He proposed the ten major challenges of HarmonyOS and was responsible for a series of key technologies in Hongmeng (software operating system and corresponding product solutions), and implemented the commercialization of 1+8 device products (including Hongmeng Intelligent Driving). In the field of mobile communications (3G/4G/5G), he led the packet core network team to successfully develop the main products. He has 50+ patents (international and domestic) and journal papers.
